# Code Style

- from __future__ import annotations at top of every src/ module
- Type hints required on all function signatures
- Docstrings required on all public functions and classes (one-line minimum)
- Use pathlib.Path, never os.path
- No bare except: — always except SomeError as e:
- No print() in src/ — use logging.getLogger(__name__)
- Constants in UPPER_SNAKE_CASE at module level
- Never hardcode 80 (n_muscles) or 322 (smplx_dim) — read from config or muscle_names.json
- Document tensor shapes in comments: # [B, T, N_muscles]
- Use einops.rearrange for non-trivial reshaping
- Atomic writes: write to .tmp then Path.rename() for checkpoints
- Text files: always encoding="utf-8"

## Testing
- Every public function in src/ has at least one unit test
- Tests must NOT require GPU, network, or real dataset
- Use synthetic tensors: batch=2, T=16, N=80
- Mock heavy imports with unittest.mock.patch

## What NOT to do
- Do NOT modify anything under vendor/
- Do NOT call model.generate() inside DDP-wrapped module
- Do NOT use torch.nn.DataParallel — DDP only
- Do NOT call plt.show() — use fig.savefig(buf) with BytesIO
